_source.title: Instructions
_source.visState:
{"title":"Instructions","type":"markdown","params":{"fontSize":12,"openLinksInNewTab":false,"markdown":"# Syslog and SSH logging Dashboard

## How To

Brief overview and instructions.

### 1. How to find server error quickly:

1. Click on the Search box and select the server to look at. (multiple servers can be selected).
2. Select the log name on the search box to refine search to a particular log. 
3. The Log table will then populate with all the relevant error matches pertaining to the selected server and log. 

```bash

Server time 	     Log 	                      Process name 	Count 
_______________________________________________________________________________________________
Jan 22 22:04:04	     ext4 fs error system crash	      devops	        1
```
_***Please Note***: Depending on how big the ES index or indices loading results may take a while. Vertical scaling ElasticSearch can be a viable solution updating memory when running `deploy_elk.sh`script. If vertical scaling doesn't work, horizontal scaling me be needed._"},"aggs":[]}
